In Minecraft, you can build anything from simple shelters to complex machines and contraptions using a variety of blocks2 such as dirt, stone, wood, and ore3 You can also mine resources, as the name suggests, crafting tools, weapons, and other items4 to help you survive in this blocky world5 

The game has both creative and survival modes6 In Creative mode, you have unlimited resources and the ability to fly, allowing you to focus solely on building7 While in Survival mode8, you'll need to gather resources, craft items, and build shelter to protect yourself from monsters that come out at night9 The game's pixelated graphics10 add to its charm11
